Heard of, to the extent that Gametek are still playing the game of sliding
release dates with it.  That is, they still say it will be released, in a
few weeks' time; a few weeks later, it will be released in a few weeks'
time; etc.

Has anyone heard of a pirate version of the Atari ST version?  I've read
here about the Amiga version being pirated before it was released.  I've
heard of a pirate version for the PC, presumably also pre-release because
it had even more bugs than those discussed here (apparently you can't sell
the 1MW pulse laser from the Eagle fighter because the shipyard doesn't
think you have one).  I have not heard of a pirate version for the Atari ST.
Guess which format hasn't been released yet.

Disclaimer: I'm not looking for a pirate copy for the Atari ST, or any other
machine.  I'm looking for information about them.  What I would like to know
is, did Gametek release Frontier on the PC and Amiga, perhaps prematurely,
because pirate copies were already circulating and they were worried that too
many people would get pirate copies before they could get real copies?

