Well, alot of people seem to have this problem, but in a total of somewhere
over 100 missions I've only ever had them not show up twice, and both times I
fixed that by restoring an old save and being sneaky.  Here's the deal;

The standard way to catch your target is to land at the port they are going to
be coming out of.  Make sure you have the right day (I once got there on
January 17 for a February 17 assassination).  Wait until the correct day and a
short time before the scheduled departure (how short ranges from 30 minutes to
30 seconds depending on personal preference really).  Now the important parts;

1:  Do not stay directly over the launch site.  If you do they will often not
come out until you move.  The way to spot this problem is if the launch bay
stays open after you leave (if you fly out and stop immediatly it will do this)
Get out of the way and the target will come out.

2:  The target usually comes out within 2 or 3 seconds before or after the
appointed time (see 1 above for an exception... there they come out a few
seconds after you get out of the way).

3:  The target usually does not stick around long.  95% of the time they will
either hyperspace or turn around and go right back to the base (I once had a
target in a Panther at the 82 Eridani system... the only base within range was
the one he came out of... could only hyperspace to one other system and there
were no bases there.  Thus he just came out and turned around and went back...
no matter what.  Had to use the missile bug to kill him right there).
Sometimes they will fly to another base in the same system... this is great but
don't count on it.

4:  If you are too far from the base you will never even see them come out most
of the time.  In this case you want to watch your system map (f2-f2).  At the
time they are set to depart (or right around then) a ship dot will appear on
the planet.  Target it and use communications (f4) to verify that it is the
correct ship (don't place a call, just get the 'Send message to ship xx-yyy'
message and check the registration number)

5:  Anywhere that it still displays your altitude should be close enough to
spot the target.  I prefer to hover over the base at about 10,000.  If they are
leaving an orbital station you want to still be able to make out the writing on
the station... maybe 6-10 km or thereabouts.


If you do all this (right date, exact time, close enough to see or checking
system map (f2-f2)) and they STILL don't show up then you've probably got what
I call the 'forewarned' feature.  I >THINK< this occurs based on a couple of
things.  First if the system the target is at is right next to the system where
the bulletin was posted (a target in Vequess on the bulletin board in Facece
for instance) then they might well hear about it.  Second, if you just sit
around outside the base for a couple of days they are likely to figure it out.
This is characterized by a couple of things;

A:  If you are waiting in the station the police suddenly pounce on you (often
days before the event) for 'piracy and murder.'  If this happens you have to
pay the fine and the target WILL NOT show up.  My suggestion... reload an old
save.

B:  If you are waiting outside the station for a long time the target will just
not show up.  Again I suggest reloading.

FIX:  Time your arrival.  Figure out how long the jump to the system and flight
to the base will take and then wait around in a neighboring system.  Time your
arrival at the target's base for about 5 hours before departure.  Land at the
base, refuel, get all your missiles stocked up, and launch a short time before
the target... they should come out as normal.


If you do ALL this and they still don't come out then all I can say is that it
must be a bug in your version because via this method I have NEVER failed to
complete an assassination.
-- 
