>Is it just me or have loads of people found this "bug"?

(also have version 1.00 and use wormhole to get to location
 in two jumps)

I found that the station missions are the worst.  Also
those at systems that have more than one star.  The
missions at stations would always be iffy.  The best
method is to hang around for a while at the point
where you jumped in, then make your run so you
will only have to wait at dock for less than two
days.  Take off about 15 minutes before the time,
and I usually backward thrust (-5.2 kmh) at almost
90 degrees from the door.  This seems to work for
me.

Planetary missions, you just take off early, climb
to 12,000km (jump range), and then wait around for
the target.  You will need to run accelerated time,
at normal time your ship will rise or drop.  I
usually kill the target before they jump and pay
the fine.  (missile, then kill = 600cr fine).

I also will take 2-5 missions at a time.  I make
sure that I have enough time between to get there,
and make sure that they are all single star,
and planetary if possible.

It took me 26 assassinations to move to lord, but
I wasn't immediately offered photograph missions.
I ran 6 more assassinations before I got recon.

