Bzzzt.  Spin again.  The program does NOT shut down the OS.  There are 3 ways
to crash Frontier that I am aware of;

1:  There are a couple of obcure bugs in the assassination sequence that can
cause a crash... I doubt you've gotten that far, so this is out. 

2:  You've got the stack size set too low so the game crashes at various
intervals when you do things it can't handle.  100000 seems to work fine.

3:  You've got processes running in the background and one of them suddenly
does something (open a new window for instance) that makes Frontier freak out.

Since you were under the mistaken impression that the OS was shut down it might
be number 3.  It can't be number 1 because that only occurs in specific
instances when you are a ways along in the game... not at random.  My money is
on option 2 though... seems to be the cause of 99.99% of the 'frontier sucks it
keeps crashing on me' cries.

Other than that it might be some problem I haven't seen.  Probably hardware
related.
