Summary: A scientific explanation of some of the stranger features in Frontier


There have been a lot of posts recently about some features in Frontier.
After having tried these I have come up with a plausible explanation for these.

Starting with the wormholes:
As you all know, the Universe is wrapped into itself. This causes 'mirror' 
galaxies to appear at set distances. Hyperspace, which is a completely
different universe, is also wrapped into itself, but this wrapping is
much tighter. I think that it's about 200 ly in diameter.
Because during a hyperspace-jump the hyperspace is 'mapped' to the real space,
'mirrors' of your position are formed about every 650 ly, so that you can
jump this great distance with little fuel.

About the passenger cabins:
If you sell a ship with a passenger on board, the shipyard actually doesn't
complain. But the passenger is quite displeased with the fact that you sell
a ship with him/her on board. Because of lack of care from the government
you don't have any problem with this. The passenger will then buy the ship 
back from the shipyard for you, so in fact you are costing the passenger
money!

Some other bugs actually are bugs, In your on-board AI which you inherited
from your grandpa, so it's quite old (and thus as smart as a horses ass)
This causes various bugs, such as the bulletin-board bug and the songs
which you hear while piloting. Because an AI is something personal,
you are stuck with it.

This is all I can think of right now, so if you have any questions, feel
free to ask.

See you in BrabenSpace !
