Hi,

I've been playing Frontier on my Amiga 1000 for about a week
now and I've had no crashes.  The only "bug" I've seen is
in the Bulletin Board which sometimes won't let you scroll
backwards.  This is solved by waiting until midnight when
the board is refreshed.  Just accelerate game time with the
>>>>> button.  So far it's lots of fun.  I have 8.5MB of
memory and it's installed on one of my hard disks, with
stack set at 100000, I have no problems with the software.
You do have to turn off any mouse accelerators and screen
blankers, but that's true with a lot of games.  I use the
highest detail level and find that response is fine. I have
version 1.05 or some such number.  Combat is difficult
with your initial ship so stay in the SOL <--> Barnard
system running Luxury Goods to Barnard and Robots and
Computers to SOL.  Save your money and upgrade your ship
several times before you take on aggressors.  No one will
attack you in the SOL or Barnard systems. So sell your
missiles and scanner, in fact everything except the autopilot
which you need to land.  You can even get rid of the atmospheric
shields if you're willing to stick to space stations and airless
moons.  This gives you the most room for cargo to make money so
you can get a bigger ship.  Good luck, have fun.

-mjw-

P.S. I also highly recommend Hired Guns 

