I pretty much keep my Amiga in PAL anyway, so I can't really verify 
whether or not this program runs in PAL.  If you have a commodore monitor
it is pretty easy to adjust the vertical height knob to get the whole
screen.  The bottom of the screen is filled with controls, so without 
being able to see them the game would be pretty useless.  There isn't 
any difference in computer speed between PAL and NTSC unless you count
the fact that more pixels on the screen means that more need to be drawn
for each frame.


