Well, I was just getting a bit tired with flying boring message
missions and doing the occational very irritating and time-wasting (not
to mention potentially disasterous if they didnt turn up) assassination
missions and then the photograph missions appeared. I have to say its
breathed a whole new life into the game which was going the original
elite way (i.e. get to dangerous or deadly and there was no
interest/challenge left (except doing thargoid invasions with a pulse
laser!)).

Wow, so many ships attacking at once. Pity they are all so small
(lightweight ones).

Does anyone know:
(a) Roughly what distance you need to photograph from? I did it quite
close but I wasnt sure of the distance.
(b) How good a "kill" is of the defence craft? i.e. are they good for
boosting your elite rating or are they like police vipers which do
nothing(?)?
(c) Whats the fastest way of getting near to the bases? I got to the
stage where it was slightly larger than the pixel it starts as and then
the fighters got launched and I couldnt use my time streamer anymore
*8-(
(d) How many more different sorts of mission are there? Or is this the
last different type.

Anyway, for all you Frontier people looking for a bigger challenge, or
at the very least an entertaining dog-fight/slaugher for as long as you
want - do a recon mission *8-)

Cheers
Jonathan

